#. class="division">
msgctxt "dn22:1.1"
msgid "Dīgha Nikāya 22"
msgstr "Long Discourses 22"

#. </p><h1>
msgctxt "dn22:2.1"
msgid "Mahāsatipaṭṭhānasutta"
msgstr "The Longer Discourse on Mindfulness Meditation"

#. </h1></div><p><a class="sc" id="1"></a><a class="wp" id="wp1"></a><a
#. class="pts" id="pts2.290"></a>
msgctxt "dn22:3.1"
msgid "<span class=\"evam\">Evaṃ me sutaṃ—​</span>"
msgstr "<span class=”evam”>So I have heard.</span>"

msgctxt "dn22:3.2"
msgid ""
"ekaṃ samayaṃ bhagavā kurūsu viharati kammāsadhammaṃ nāma kurūnaṃ nigamo."
msgstr ""
"At one time the Buddha was staying in the land of the Kurus, near the Kuru "
"town named Kammāsadamma."

msgctxt "dn22:3.3"
msgid "Tatra kho bhagavā bhikkhū āmantesi:"
msgstr "There the Buddha addressed the mendicants: "

msgctxt "dn22:3.4"
msgid "“bhikkhavo”ti."
msgstr "“Mendicants!”"

#. VAR: Bhaddante”ti → bhadanteti (bj, s1-3, km, pts1)
msgctxt "dn22:3.5"
msgid "“Bhaddante”ti te bhikkhū bhagavato paccassosuṃ."
msgstr "“Venerable sir,” they replied. "

msgctxt "dn22:3.6"
msgid "Bhagavā etadavoca:"
msgstr "The Buddha said this:  "

#. </p><p><a class="sc" id="2"></a>
msgctxt "dn22:4.1"
msgid ""
"“Ekāyano ayaṃ, bhikkhave, maggo sattānaṃ visuddhiyā, sokaparidevānaṃ "
"samatikkamāya dukkhadomanassānaṃ atthaṅgamāya ñāyassa adhigamāya nibbānassa "
"sacchikiriyāya, yadidaṃ cattāro satipaṭṭhānā."
msgstr ""
"“Mendicants, the four kinds of mindfulness meditation are the path to "
"convergence. They are in order to purify sentient beings, to get past sorrow "
"and crying, to make an end of pain and sadness, to complete the procedure, "
"and to realize extinguishment."

#. </p><p><a class="sc" id="3"></a>
msgctxt "dn22:5.1"
msgid "Katame cattāro?"
msgstr "What four? "

#, fuzzy
msgctxt "dn22:5.2"
msgid ""
"Idha, bhikkhave, bhikkhu kāye kāyānupassī viharati ātāpī sampajāno satimā "
"vineyya loke abhijjhādomanassaṃ, vedanāsu vedanānupassī viharati ātāpī "
"sampajāno satimā vineyya loke abhijjhādomanassaṃ, citte cittānupassī "
"viharati ātāpī sampajāno satimā vineyya loke abhijjhādomanassaṃ, dhammesu "
"dhammānupassī viharati ātāpī sampajāno satimā vineyya loke "
"abhijjhādomanassaṃ."
msgstr ""
"It’s when a mendicant meditates by observing an aspect of the body, keen, "
"aware, and mindful, rid of desire and aversion for the world. They meditate "
"by observing an aspect of feelings, keen, aware, and mindful, rid of desire "
"and aversion for the world. They meditate by observing an aspect of the "
"mind, keen, aware, and mindful, rid of desire and aversion for the world. "
"They meditate by observing an aspect of principles, keen, aware, and "
"mindful, rid of desire and aversion for the world."

#. </p><p class="endsection">
msgctxt "dn22:6.1"
msgid "Uddeso niṭṭhito."
msgstr ""

#. </p><h2>
msgctxt "dn22:7.1"
msgid "1. Kāyānupassanā"
msgstr "1 Observing the Body"

#. </h2><h3>
msgctxt "dn22:8.1"
msgid "1.1. Kāyānupassanāānāpānapabba"
msgstr "1.1. Mindfulness of Breathing"

#. </h3><p><a class="sc" id="4"></a><a class="wp" id="wp2"></a><a class="pts"
#. id="pts2.291"></a>
msgctxt "dn22:9.1"
msgid "Kathañca pana, bhikkhave, bhikkhu kāye kāyānupassī viharati?"
msgstr "And how does a mendicant meditate by observing an aspect of the body?"

msgctxt "dn22:9.2"
msgid ""
"Idha, bhikkhave, bhikkhu araññagato vā rukkhamūlagato vā suññāgāragato vā "
"nisīdati pallaṅkaṃ ābhujitvā ujuṃ kāyaṃ paṇidhāya parimukhaṃ satiṃ "
"upaṭṭhapetvā."
msgstr ""
"It’s when a mendicant—gone to a wilderness, or to the root of a tree, or to "
"an empty hut—sits down in the meditation posture, with their body erect, and "
"focuses their mindfulness right there."

msgctxt "dn22:9.3"
msgid "So satova assasati, satova passasati."
msgstr "Just mindful, they breathe in. Mindful, they breathe out."

#. </p><p><a class="sc" id="5"></a>
msgctxt "dn22:10.1"
msgid ""
"Dīghaṃ vā assasanto ‘dīghaṃ assasāmī’ti pajānāti, dīghaṃ vā passasanto ‘"
"dīghaṃ passasāmī’ti pajānāti."
msgstr ""
"When breathing in heavily they know: ‘I’m breathing in heavily.’ When "
"breathing out heavily they know: ‘I’m breathing out heavily.’"

#. </p><p><a class="sc" id="6"></a>
msgctxt "dn22:11.1"
msgid ""
"Rassaṃ vā assasanto ‘rassaṃ assasāmī’ti pajānāti, rassaṃ vā passasanto ‘"
"rassaṃ passasāmī’ti pajānāti."
msgstr ""
"When breathing in lightly they know: ‘I’m breathing in lightly.’ When "
"breathing out lightly they know: ‘I’m breathing out lightly.’"

#. </p><p><a class="sc" id="7"></a>
msgctxt "dn22:12.1"
msgid ""
"‘Sabbakāyapaṭisaṃvedī assasissāmī’ti sikkhati, ‘sabbakāyapaṭisaṃvedī "
"passasissāmī’ti sikkhati."
msgstr ""
"They practice breathing in experiencing the whole body. They practice "
"breathing out experiencing the whole body."

#. </p><p><a class="sc" id="8"></a>
msgctxt "dn22:13.1"
msgid ""
"‘Passambhayaṃ kāyasaṅkhāraṃ assasissāmī’ti sikkhati, ‘passambhayaṃ "
"kāyasaṅkhāraṃ passasissāmī’ti sikkhati."
msgstr ""
"They practice breathing in stilling the body’s motion. They practice "
"breathing out stilling the body’s motion."

#. </p><p><a class="sc" id="9"></a>
msgctxt "dn22:14.1"
msgid ""
"Seyyathāpi, bhikkhave, dakkho bhamakāro vā bhamakārantevāsī vā dīghaṃ vā "
"añchanto ‘dīghaṃ añchāmī’ti pajānāti, rassaṃ vā añchanto ‘rassaṃ añchāmī’ti "
"pajānāti;"
msgstr ""
"It’s like a skilled carpenter or carpenter’s apprentice. When making a deep "
"cut they know ‘I’m making a deep cut,’ and when making a shallow cut they "
"know ‘I’m making a shallow cut.’"

msgctxt "dn22:14.2"
msgid ""
"evameva kho, bhikkhave, bhikkhu dīghaṃ vā assasanto ‘dīghaṃ assasāmī’ti "
"pajānāti, dīghaṃ vā passasanto ‘dīghaṃ passasāmī’ti pajānāti, rassaṃ vā "
"assasanto ‘rassaṃ assasāmī’ti pajānāti, rassaṃ vā passasanto ‘rassaṃ "
"passasāmī’ti pajānāti."
msgstr ""

msgctxt "dn22:14.3"
msgid ""
"‘Sabbakāyapaṭisaṃvedī assasissāmī’ti sikkhati, ‘sabbakāyapaṭisaṃvedī "
"passasissāmī’ti sikkhati, ‘passambhayaṃ kāyasaṅkhāraṃ assasissāmī’ti "
"sikkhati, ‘passambhayaṃ kāyasaṅkhāraṃ passasissāmī’ti sikkhati."
msgstr ""

#. </p><p><a class="sc" id="10"></a><a class="pts" id="pts2.292"></a>
msgctxt "dn22:15.1"
msgid ""
"Iti ajjhattaṃ vā kāye kāyānupassī viharati, bahiddhā vā kāye kāyānupassī "
"viharati, ajjhattabahiddhā vā kāye kāyānupassī viharati."
msgstr ""
"And so they meditate observing an aspect of the body internally, externally, "
"and both internally and externally."

msgctxt "dn22:15.2"
msgid ""
"Samudayadhammānupassī vā kāyasmiṃ viharati, vayadhammānupassī vā kāyasmiṃ "
"viharati, samudayavayadhammānupassī vā kāyasmiṃ viharati."
msgstr ""
"They meditate observing the body as liable to originate, as liable to "
"vanish, and as liable to both originate and vanish."

#, fuzzy
msgctxt "dn22:15.3"
msgid ""
"‘Atthi kāyo’ti vā panassa sati paccupaṭṭhitā hoti yāvadeva ñāṇamattāya "
"paṭissatimattāya anissito ca viharati, na ca kiñci loke upādiyati."
msgstr ""
"Or mindfulness is established that the body exists, to the extent necessary "
"for knowledge and mindfulness. They meditate independent, not grasping at "
"anything in the world."

#. VAR: Evampi kho → evampi (s1-3, km, pts1)
msgctxt "dn22:15.4"
msgid "Evampi kho, bhikkhave, bhikkhu kāye kāyānupassī viharati."
msgstr "That’s how a mendicant meditates by observing an aspect of the body."

#. </p><p class="endsection">
msgctxt "dn22:16.1"
msgid "Ānāpānapabbaṃ niṭṭhitaṃ."
msgstr ""

#. </p><h3>
msgctxt "dn22:17.1"
msgid "1.2. Kāyānupassanāiriyāpathapabba"
msgstr "1.2. The Postures"

#. </h3><p><a class="sc" id="11"></a><a class="wp" id="wp3"></a>
#, fuzzy
msgctxt "dn22:18.1"
msgid ""
"Puna caparaṃ, bhikkhave, bhikkhu gacchanto vā ‘gacchāmī’ti pajānāti, ṭhito "
"vā ‘ṭhitomhī’ti pajānāti, nisinno vā ‘nisinnomhī’ti pajānāti, sayāno vā "
"‘sayānomhī’ti pajānāti, yathā yathā vā panassa kāyo paṇihito hoti tathā "
"tathā naṃ pajānāti."
msgstr ""
"Furthermore, when a mendicant is walking they know ‘I am walking’. When "
"standing they know ‘I am standing’. When sitting they know ‘I am sitting’. "
"And when lying down they know ‘I am lying down’. Whatever posture their body "
"is in, they know it."

#. </p><p><a class="sc" id="12"></a>
msgctxt "dn22:19.1"
msgid ""
"Iti ajjhattaṃ vā kāye kāyānupassī viharati, bahiddhā vā kāye kāyānupassī "
"viharati, ajjhattabahiddhā vā kāye kāyānupassī viharati."
msgstr ""
"And so they meditate observing an aspect of the body internally, externally, "
"and both internally and externally."

msgctxt "dn22:19.2"
msgid ""
"Samudayadhammānupassī vā kāyasmiṃ viharati, vayadhammānupassī vā kāyasmiṃ "
"viharati, samudayavayadhammānupassī vā kāyasmiṃ viharati."
msgstr ""
"They meditate observing the body as liable to originate, as liable to "
"vanish, and as liable to both originate and vanish."

msgctxt "dn22:19.3"
msgid ""
"‘Atthi kāyo’ti vā panassa sati paccupaṭṭhitā hoti yāvadeva ñāṇamattāya "
"paṭissatimattāya anissito ca viharati, na ca kiñci loke upādiyati."
msgstr ""
"Or mindfulness is established that the body exists, to the extent necessary "
"for knowledge and mindfulness. They meditate independent, not grasping at "
"anything in the world."

msgctxt "dn22:19.4"
msgid "Evampi kho, bhikkhave, bhikkhu kāye kāyānupassī viharati."
msgstr ""
"That too is how a mendicant meditates by observing an aspect of the body."

#. </p><p class="endsection">
msgctxt "dn22:20.1"
msgid "Iriyāpathapabbaṃ niṭṭhitaṃ."
msgstr ""

#. </p><h3>
msgctxt "dn22:21.1"
msgid "1.3. Kāyānupassanāsampajānapabba"
msgstr "1.3. Situational Awareness"

#. </h3><p><a class="sc" id="13"></a><a class="wp" id="wp4"></a>
msgctxt "dn22:22.1"
msgid ""
"Puna caparaṃ, bhikkhave, bhikkhu abhikkante paṭikkante sampajānakārī hoti, "
"ālokite vilokite sampajānakārī hoti, samiñjite pasārite sampajānakārī hoti, "
"saṅghāṭipattacīvaradhāraṇe sampajānakārī hoti, asite pīte khāyite sāyite "
"sampajānakārī hoti, uccārapassāvakamme sampajānakārī hoti, gate ṭhite "
"nisinne sutte jāgarite bhāsite tuṇhībhāve sampajānakārī hoti."
msgstr ""
"Furthermore, a mendicant acts with situational awareness when going out and "
"coming back; when looking ahead and aside; when bending and extending the "
"limbs; when bearing the outer robe, bowl and robes; when eating, drinking, "
"chewing, and tasting; when urinating and defecating; when walking, standing, "
"sitting, sleeping, waking, speaking, and keeping silent."

#. </p><p><a class="sc" id="14"></a><a class="pts" id="pts2.293"></a>
msgctxt "dn22:23.1"
msgid "Iti ajjhattaṃ vā …"
msgstr "And so they meditate observing an aspect of the body internally …"

msgctxt "dn22:23.2"
msgid "pe …"
msgstr ""

msgctxt "dn22:23.3"
msgid "evampi kho, bhikkhave, bhikkhu kāye kāyānupassī viharati."
msgstr ""
"That too is how a mendicant meditates by observing an aspect of the body."

#. </p><p class="endsection">
msgctxt "dn22:24.1"
msgid "Sampajānapabbaṃ niṭṭhitaṃ."
msgstr ""

#. </p><h3>
msgctxt "dn22:25.1"
msgid "1.4. Kāyānupassanāpaṭikūlamanasikārapabba"
msgstr "1.4. Focusing on the Repulsive"

#. </h3><p><a class="sc" id="15"></a><a class="wp" id="wp5"></a>
msgctxt "dn22:26.1"
msgid ""
"Puna caparaṃ, bhikkhave, bhikkhu imameva kāyaṃ uddhaṃ pādatalā adho "
"kesamatthakā tacapariyantaṃ pūraṃ nānappakārassa asucino paccavekkhati:"
msgstr ""
"Furthermore, a mendicant examines their own body, up from the soles of the "
"feet and down from the tips of the hairs, wrapped in skin and full of many "
"kinds of filth."

#. VAR: udariyaṃ karīsaṃ → karīsaṃ matthaluṅgaṃ (mr)
msgctxt "dn22:26.2"
msgid ""
"‘atthi imasmiṃ kāye kesā lomā nakhā dantā taco, maṃsaṃ nhāru aṭṭhi "
"aṭṭhimiñjaṃ vakkaṃ, hadayaṃ yakanaṃ kilomakaṃ pihakaṃ papphāsaṃ, antaṃ "
"antaguṇaṃ udariyaṃ karīsaṃ, pittaṃ semhaṃ pubbo lohitaṃ sedo medo, assu vasā "
"kheḷo siṅghāṇikā lasikā muttan’ti."
msgstr ""
"‘In this body there is head hair, body hair, nails, teeth, skin, flesh, "
"sinews, bones, bone marrow, kidneys, heart, liver, diaphragm, spleen, lungs, "
"intestines, mesentry, undigested food, feces, bile, phlegm, pus, blood, "
"sweat, fat, tears, grease, saliva, snot, synovial fluid, urine.’ "

#. </p><p><a class="sc" id="16"></a><a class="pts" id="pts2.294"></a>
#. VAR: putoḷi → mūtoḷī (s1-3, km) | mutoli (pts1)
msgctxt "dn22:27.1"
msgid ""
"Seyyathāpi, bhikkhave, ubhatomukhā putoḷi pūrā nānāvihitassa dhaññassa, "
"seyyathidaṃ—"
msgstr ""
"It’s as if there were a bag with openings at both ends, filled with various "
"kinds of grains, such as"

msgctxt "dn22:27.2"
msgid "sālīnaṃ vīhīnaṃ muggānaṃ māsānaṃ tilānaṃ taṇḍulānaṃ."
msgstr "fine rice, wheat, mung beans, peas, sesame, and ordinary rice."

msgctxt "dn22:27.3"
msgid "Tamenaṃ cakkhumā puriso muñcitvā paccavekkheyya:"
msgstr ""
"And someone with good eyesight were to open it and examine the contents:"

msgctxt "dn22:27.4"
msgid "‘ime sālī, ime vīhī ime muggā ime māsā ime tilā ime taṇḍulā’ti."
msgstr ""
"‘These grains are fine rice, these are wheat, these are mung beans, these "
"are peas, these are sesame, and these are ordinary rice.’"

msgctxt "dn22:27.5"
msgid ""
"Evameva kho, bhikkhave, bhikkhu imameva kāyaṃ uddhaṃ pādatalā adho "
"kesamatthakā tacapariyantaṃ pūraṃ nānappakārassa asucino paccavekkhati:"
msgstr ""

msgctxt "dn22:27.6"
msgid "‘atthi imasmiṃ kāye kesā lomā …"
msgstr ""

msgctxt "dn22:27.7"
msgid "pe …"
msgstr ""

msgctxt "dn22:27.8"
msgid "muttan’ti."
msgstr ""

#. </p><p><a class="sc" id="17"></a>
msgctxt "dn22:28.1"
msgid "Iti ajjhattaṃ vā …"
msgstr "And so they meditate observing an aspect of the body internally …"

msgctxt "dn22:28.2"
msgid "pe …"
msgstr ""

msgctxt "dn22:28.3"
msgid "evampi kho, bhikkhave, bhikkhu kāye kāyānupassī viharati."
msgstr ""
"That too is how a mendicant meditates by observing an aspect of the body."

#. </p><p class="endsection">
msgctxt "dn22:29.1"
msgid "Paṭikūlamanasikārapabbaṃ niṭṭhitaṃ."
msgstr ""

#. </p><h3>
msgctxt "dn22:30.1"
msgid "1.5. Kāyānupassanādhātumanasikārapabba"
msgstr "1.5. Focusing on the Elements"

#. </h3><p><a class="sc" id="18"></a><a class="wp" id="wp6"></a>
msgctxt "dn22:31.1"
msgid ""
"Puna caparaṃ, bhikkhave, bhikkhu imameva kāyaṃ yathāṭhitaṃ yathāpaṇihitaṃ "
"dhātuso paccavekkhati:"
msgstr ""
"Furthermore, a mendicant examines their own body, whatever its placement or "
"posture, according to the elements:"

msgctxt "dn22:31.2"
msgid "‘atthi imasmiṃ kāye pathavīdhātu āpodhātu tejodhātu vāyodhātū’ti."
msgstr ""
"‘In this body there is the earth element, the water element, the fire "
"element, and the air element.’"

#. </p><p><a class="sc" id="19"></a>
msgctxt "dn22:32.1"
msgid ""
"Seyyathāpi, bhikkhave, dakkho goghātako vā goghātakantevāsī vā gāviṃ "
"vadhitvā catumahāpathe bilaso vibhajitvā nisinno assa;"
msgstr ""
"It’s as if a skilled butcher or butcher’s apprentice were to kill a cow and "
"sit down at the crossroads with the meat cut into portions."

msgctxt "dn22:32.2"
msgid ""
"evameva kho, bhikkhave, bhikkhu imameva kāyaṃ yathāṭhitaṃ yathāpaṇihitaṃ "
"dhātuso paccavekkhati:"
msgstr ""

msgctxt "dn22:32.3"
msgid "‘atthi imasmiṃ kāye pathavīdhātu āpodhātu tejodhātu vāyodhātū’ti."
msgstr ""

#. </p><p><a class="sc" id="20"></a><a class="pts" id="pts2.295"></a>
msgctxt "dn22:33.1"
msgid "Iti ajjhattaṃ vā kāye kāyānupassī viharati …"
msgstr "And so they meditate observing an aspect of the body internally …"

msgctxt "dn22:33.2"
msgid "pe …"
msgstr ""

msgctxt "dn22:33.3"
msgid "evampi kho, bhikkhave, bhikkhu kāye kāyānupassī viharati."
msgstr ""
"That too is how a mendicant meditates by observing an aspect of the body."

#. </p><p class="endsection">
msgctxt "dn22:34.1"
msgid "Dhātumanasikārapabbaṃ niṭṭhitaṃ."
msgstr ""

#. </p><h3>
msgctxt "dn22:35.1"
msgid "1.6. Kāyānupassanānavasivathikapabba"
msgstr "1.6. The Charnel Ground Contemplations"

#. </h3><p><a class="sc" id="21"></a><a class="wp" id="wp7"></a>
msgctxt "dn22:36.1"
msgid ""
"Puna caparaṃ, bhikkhave, bhikkhu seyyathāpi passeyya sarīraṃ sivathikāya "
"chaḍḍitaṃ ekāhamataṃ vā dvīhamataṃ vā tīhamataṃ vā uddhumātakaṃ vinīlakaṃ "
"vipubbakajātaṃ."
msgstr ""
"Furthermore, suppose a mendicant were to see a corpse thrown in a charnel "
"ground. And it had been dead for one, two, or three days, bloated, livid, "
"and festering."

msgctxt "dn22:36.2"
msgid "So imameva kāyaṃ upasaṃharati:"
msgstr "They’d compare it with their own body:"

msgctxt "dn22:36.3"
msgid "‘ayampi kho kāyo evaṃdhammo evaṃbhāvī evaṃanatīto’ti."
msgstr ""
"‘This body is also of that same nature, that same kind, and cannot go beyond "
"that.’"

msgctxt "dn22:36.4"
msgid "Iti ajjhattaṃ vā …"
msgstr "And so they meditate observing an aspect of the body internally …"

msgctxt "dn22:36.5"
msgid "pe …"
msgstr ""

msgctxt "dn22:36.6"
msgid ""
"evampi kho, bhikkhave, bhikkhu kāye kāyānupassī viharati. <span class=\""
"brnum\">(1)</span>"
msgstr ""
"That too is how a mendicant meditates by observing an aspect of the body."

#. </p><p><a class="sc" id="22"></a><a class="wp" id="wp8"></a><a class="pts"
#. id="pts2.296"></a>
#. VAR:  kaṅkehi vā khajjamānaṃ sunakhehi vā khajjamānaṃ byagghehi vā
#. khajjamānaṃ dīpīhi vā khajjamānaṃ siṅgālehi vā khajjamānaṃ →  suvānehi vā
#. khajjamānaṃ sigālehi vā khajjamānaṃ (sī1, syā1-3, kaṃ), supāṇehi vā
#. khajjamānaṃ sigālehi vā khajjamānaṃ (pā1)
msgctxt "dn22:37.1"
msgid ""
"Puna caparaṃ, bhikkhave, bhikkhu seyyathāpi passeyya sarīraṃ sivathikāya "
"chaḍḍitaṃ kākehi vā khajjamānaṃ kulalehi vā khajjamānaṃ gijjhehi vā "
"khajjamānaṃ kaṅkehi vā khajjamānaṃ sunakhehi vā khajjamānaṃ byagghehi vā "
"khajjamānaṃ dīpīhi vā khajjamānaṃ siṅgālehi vā khajjamānaṃ vividhehi vā "
"pāṇakajātehi khajjamānaṃ."
msgstr ""
"Furthermore, suppose they were to see a corpse thrown in a charnel ground "
"being devoured by crows, hawks, vultures, herons, dogs, tigers, leopards, "
"jackals, and many kinds of little creatures."

msgctxt "dn22:37.2"
msgid "So imameva kāyaṃ upasaṃharati:"
msgstr "They’d compare it with their own body:"

msgctxt "dn22:37.3"
msgid "‘ayampi kho kāyo evaṃdhammo evaṃbhāvī evaṃanatīto’ti."
msgstr ""
"‘This body is also of that same nature, that same kind, and cannot go beyond "
"that.’"

msgctxt "dn22:37.4"
msgid "Iti ajjhattaṃ vā …"
msgstr "And so they meditate observing an aspect of the body internally …"

msgctxt "dn22:37.5"
msgid "pe …"
msgstr ""

msgctxt "dn22:37.6"
msgid ""
"evampi kho, bhikkhave, bhikkhu kāye kāyānupassī viharati. <span class=\""
"brnum\">(2)</span>"
msgstr ""
"That too is how a mendicant meditates by observing an aspect of the body."

#. </p><p><a class="sc" id="23"></a>
msgctxt "dn22:38.1"
msgid ""
"Puna caparaṃ, bhikkhave, bhikkhu seyyathāpi passeyya sarīraṃ sivathikāya "
"chaḍḍitaṃ aṭṭhikasaṅkhalikaṃ samaṃsalohitaṃ nhārusambandhaṃ …"
msgstr ""
"Furthermore, suppose they were to see a corpse thrown in a charnel ground, a "
"skeleton with flesh and blood, held together by sinews …"

msgctxt "dn22:38.2"
msgid "pe … <span class=\"brnum\">(3)</span>"
msgstr ""

#. </p><p><a class="sc" id="24"></a>
msgctxt "dn22:39.1"
msgid "Aṭṭhikasaṅkhalikaṃ nimaṃsalohitamakkhitaṃ nhārusambandhaṃ …"
msgstr ""
"A skeleton without flesh but smeared with blood, and held together by sinews "
"…"

msgctxt "dn22:39.2"
msgid "pe … <span class=\"brnum\">(4)</span>"
msgstr ""

#. </p><p><a class="sc" id="25"></a>
msgctxt "dn22:40.1"
msgid "Aṭṭhikasaṅkhalikaṃ apagatamaṃsalohitaṃ nhārusambandhaṃ …"
msgstr "A skeleton rid of flesh and blood, held together by sinews …"

msgctxt "dn22:40.2"
msgid "pe … <span class=\"brnum\">(5)</span>"
msgstr ""

#. </p><p><a class="sc" id="26"></a><a class="pts" id="pts2.297"></a>
#. VAR:  aññena phāsukaṭṭhikaṃ aññena piṭṭhiṭṭhikaṃ aññena khandhaṭṭhikaṃ →
#. aññena kaṭaṭṭhikaṃ aññena piṭṭhaṭṭhikaṃ aññena kaṇḍakaṭṭhikaṃ aññena
#. phāsukaṭṭhikaṃ aññena uraṭṭhikaṃ aññena aṃsaṭṭhikaṃ aññena bāhuṭṭhikaṃ
#. (syā1-3, kaṃ)
#. VAR:  aññena kaṭiṭṭhikaṃ →  aññena piṭṭhiṭṭhikaṃ aññena kaṭaṭṭhikaṃ aññena
#. khandhaṭṭhikaṃ aññena gīvaṭṭhikaṃ (sī1)
msgctxt "dn22:41.1"
msgid ""
"Aṭṭhikāni apagatasambandhāni disā vidisā vikkhittāni, aññena hatthaṭṭhikaṃ "
"aññena pādaṭṭhikaṃ aññena gopphakaṭṭhikaṃ aññena jaṅghaṭṭhikaṃ aññena "
"ūruṭṭhikaṃ aññena kaṭiṭṭhikaṃ aññena phāsukaṭṭhikaṃ aññena piṭṭhiṭṭhikaṃ "
"aññena khandhaṭṭhikaṃ aññena gīvaṭṭhikaṃ aññena hanukaṭṭhikaṃ aññena "
"dantaṭṭhikaṃ aññena sīsakaṭāhaṃ."
msgstr ""
"Bones without sinews scattered in every direction. Here a hand-bone, there a "
"foot-bone, here a shin-bone, there a thigh-bone, here a hip-bone, there a "
"rib-bone, here a back-bone, there an arm-bone, here a neck-bone, there a jaw-"
"bone, here a tooth, there the skull … "

msgctxt "dn22:41.2"
msgid "So imameva kāyaṃ upasaṃharati:"
msgstr ""

msgctxt "dn22:41.3"
msgid "‘ayampi kho kāyo evaṃdhammo evaṃbhāvī evaṃanatīto’ti."
msgstr ""

msgctxt "dn22:41.4"
msgid "Iti ajjhattaṃ vā …"
msgstr ""

msgctxt "dn22:41.5"
msgid "pe …"
msgstr ""

msgctxt "dn22:41.6"
msgid "viharati. <span class=\"brnum\">(6)</span>"
msgstr ""

#. </p><p><a class="sc" id="27"></a><a class="wp" id="wp10"></a>
msgctxt "dn22:42.1"
msgid ""
"Puna caparaṃ, bhikkhave, bhikkhu seyyathāpi passeyya sarīraṃ sivathikāya "
"chaḍḍitaṃ aṭṭhikāni setāni saṅkhavaṇṇapaṭibhāgāni …"
msgstr "White bones, the color of shells … "

msgctxt "dn22:42.2"
msgid "pe … <span class=\"brnum\">(7)</span>"
msgstr ""

#. </p><p><a class="sc" id="28"></a>
msgctxt "dn22:43.1"
msgid "Aṭṭhikāni puñjakitāni terovassikāni …"
msgstr "Decrepit bones, heaped in a pile … "

msgctxt "dn22:43.2"
msgid "pe … <span class=\"brnum\">(8)</span>"
msgstr ""

#. </p><p><a class="sc" id="29"></a><a class="pts" id="pts2.298"></a>
msgctxt "dn22:44.1"
msgid "Aṭṭhikāni pūtīni cuṇṇakajātāni."
msgstr "Bones rotted and crumbled to powder."

msgctxt "dn22:44.2"
msgid "So imameva kāyaṃ upasaṃharati:"
msgstr "They’d compare it with their own body:"

msgctxt "dn22:44.3"
msgid "‘ayampi kho kāyo evaṃdhammo evaṃbhāvī evaṃanatīto’ti."
msgstr ""
"‘This body is also of that same nature, that same kind, and cannot go beyond "
"that.’"

msgctxt "dn22:44.4"
msgid ""
"Iti ajjhattaṃ vā kāye kāyānupassī viharati, bahiddhā vā kāye kāyānupassī "
"viharati, ajjhattabahiddhā vā kāye kāyānupassī viharati."
msgstr ""
"And so they meditate observing an aspect of the body internally, externally, "
"and both internally and externally."

msgctxt "dn22:44.5"
msgid ""
"Samudayadhammānupassī vā kāyasmiṃ viharati, vayadhammānupassī vā kāyasmiṃ "
"viharati, samudayavayadhammānupassī vā kāyasmiṃ viharati."
msgstr ""
"They meditate observing the body as liable to originate, as liable to "
"vanish, and as liable to both originate and vanish."

msgctxt "dn22:44.6"
msgid ""
"‘Atthi kāyo’ti vā panassa sati paccupaṭṭhitā hoti yāvadeva ñāṇamattāya "
"paṭissatimattāya anissito ca viharati, na ca kiñci loke upādiyati."
msgstr ""
"Or mindfulness is established that the body exists, to the extent necessary "
"for knowledge and mindfulness. They meditate independent, not grasping at "
"anything in the world."

msgctxt "dn22:44.7"
msgid ""
"Evampi kho, bhikkhave, bhikkhu kāye kāyānupassī viharati. <span class=\""
"brnum\">(9)</span>"
msgstr ""
"That too is how a mendicant meditates by observing an aspect of the body."

#. </p><p class="endsection">
msgctxt "dn22:45.1"
msgid "Navasivathikapabbaṃ niṭṭhitaṃ."
msgstr ""

#. <br>
msgctxt "dn22:45.2"
msgid "Cuddasa kāyānupassanā niṭṭhitā."
msgstr ""

#. </p><h2>
msgctxt "dn22:46.1"
msgid "2. Vedanānupassanā"
msgstr "2. Observing the Feelings"

#. </h2><p><a class="sc" id="30"></a><a class="wp" id="wp11"></a>
msgctxt "dn22:47.1"
msgid "Kathañca pana, bhikkhave, bhikkhu vedanāsu vedanānupassī viharati?"
msgstr "And how does a mendicant meditate by observing an aspect of feelings?"

msgctxt "dn22:47.2"
msgid ""
"Idha, bhikkhave, bhikkhu sukhaṃ vā vedanaṃ vedayamāno ‘sukhaṃ vedanaṃ "
"vedayāmī’ti pajānāti. <span class=\"brnum\">(1)</span>"
msgstr ""
"It’s when a mendicant who feels a pleasant feeling knows: ‘I feel a pleasant "
"feeling.’"

#. </p><p><a class="sc" id="31"></a>
msgctxt "dn22:48.1"
msgid ""
"Dukkhaṃ vā vedanaṃ vedayamāno ‘dukkhaṃ vedanaṃ vedayāmī’ti pajānāti. <span "
"class=\"brnum\">(2)</span>"
msgstr ""
"When they feel a painful feeling, they know: ‘I feel a painful feeling.’"

#. </p><p><a class="sc" id="32"></a>
msgctxt "dn22:49.1"
msgid ""
"Adukkhamasukhaṃ vā vedanaṃ vedayamāno ‘adukkhamasukhaṃ vedanaṃ vedayāmī’ti "
"pajānāti. <span class=\"brnum\">(3)</span>"
msgstr ""
"When they feel a neutral feeling, they know: ‘I feel a neutral feeling.’"

#. </p><p><a class="sc" id="33"></a>
msgctxt "dn22:50.1"
msgid ""
"Sāmisaṃ vā sukhaṃ vedanaṃ vedayamāno ‘sāmisaṃ sukhaṃ vedanaṃ vedayāmī’ti "
"pajānāti. <span class=\"brnum\">(4)</span>"
msgstr ""
"When they feel a carnal pleasant feeling, they know: ‘I feel a carnal "
"pleasant feeling.’"

#. </p><p><a class="sc" id="34"></a>
msgctxt "dn22:51.1"
msgid ""
"Nirāmisaṃ vā sukhaṃ vedanaṃ vedayamāno ‘nirāmisaṃ sukhaṃ vedanaṃ vedayāmī’ti "
"pajānāti. <span class=\"brnum\">(5)</span>"
msgstr ""
"When they feel a spiritual pleasant feeling, they know: ‘I feel a spiritual "
"pleasant feeling.’"

#. </p><p><a class="sc" id="35"></a>
msgctxt "dn22:52.1"
msgid ""
"Sāmisaṃ vā dukkhaṃ vedanaṃ vedayamāno ‘sāmisaṃ dukkhaṃ vedanaṃ vedayāmī’ti "
"pajānāti. <span class=\"brnum\">(6)</span>"
msgstr ""
"When they feel a carnal painful feeling, they know: ‘I feel a carnal painful "
"feeling.’"

#. </p><p><a class="sc" id="36"></a>
msgctxt "dn22:53.1"
msgid ""
"Nirāmisaṃ vā dukkhaṃ vedanaṃ vedayamāno ‘nirāmisaṃ dukkhaṃ vedanaṃ vedayāmī’"
"ti pajānāti. <span class=\"brnum\">(7)</span>"
msgstr ""
"When they feel a spiritual painful feeling, they know: ‘I feel a spiritual "
"painful feeling.’"

#. </p><p><a class="sc" id="37"></a>
msgctxt "dn22:54.1"
msgid ""
"Sāmisaṃ vā adukkhamasukhaṃ vedanaṃ vedayamāno ‘sāmisaṃ adukkhamasukhaṃ "
"vedanaṃ vedayāmī’ti pajānāti. <span class=\"brnum\">(8)</span>"
msgstr ""
"When they feel a carnal neutral feeling, they know: ‘I feel a carnal neutral "
"feeling.’"

#. </p><p><a class="sc" id="38"></a>
msgctxt "dn22:55.1"
msgid ""
"Nirāmisaṃ vā adukkhamasukhaṃ vedanaṃ vedayamāno ‘nirāmisaṃ adukkhamasukhaṃ "
"vedanaṃ vedayāmī’ti pajānāti. <span class=\"brnum\">(9)</span>"
msgstr ""
"When they feel a spiritual neutral feeling, they know: ‘I feel a spiritual "
"neutral feeling.’"

#. </p><p><a class="sc" id="39"></a><a class="pts" id="pts2.299"></a>
msgctxt "dn22:56.1"
msgid ""
"Iti ajjhattaṃ vā vedanāsu vedanānupassī viharati, bahiddhā vā vedanāsu "
"vedanānupassī viharati, ajjhattabahiddhā vā vedanāsu vedanānupassī viharati."
msgstr ""
"And so they meditate observing an aspect of the feelings internally, "
"externally, and both internally and externally."

msgctxt "dn22:56.2"
msgid ""
"Samudayadhammānupassī vā vedanāsu viharati, vayadhammānupassī vā vedanāsu "
"viharati, samudayavayadhammānupassī vā vedanāsu viharati."
msgstr ""
"They meditate observing feelings as liable to originate, as liable to "
"vanish, and as liable to both originate and vanish."

msgctxt "dn22:56.3"
msgid ""
"‘Atthi vedanā’ti vā panassa sati paccupaṭṭhitā hoti yāvadeva ñāṇamattāya "
"paṭissatimattāya anissito ca viharati, na ca kiñci loke upādiyati."
msgstr ""
"Or mindfulness is established that feelings exist, to the extent necessary "
"for knowledge and mindfulness. They meditate independent, not grasping at "
"anything in the world."

msgctxt "dn22:56.4"
msgid "Evampi kho, bhikkhave, bhikkhu vedanāsu vedanānupassī viharati."
msgstr "That’s how a mendicant meditates by observing an aspect of feelings."

#. </p><p class="endsection">
msgctxt "dn22:57.1"
msgid "Vedanānupassanā niṭṭhitā."
msgstr ""

#. </p><h2>
msgctxt "dn22:58.1"
msgid "3. Cittānupassanā"
msgstr "3. Observing the Mind"

#. </h2><p><a class="sc" id="40"></a><a class="wp" id="wp12"></a>
msgctxt "dn22:59.1"
msgid "Kathañca pana, bhikkhave, bhikkhu citte cittānupassī viharati?"
msgstr "And how does a mendicant meditate by observing an aspect of the mind?"

msgctxt "dn22:59.2"
msgid ""
"Idha, bhikkhave, bhikkhu sarāgaṃ vā cittaṃ ‘sarāgaṃ cittan’ti pajānāti. <"
"span class=\"brnum\">(1)</span>"
msgstr "It’s when a mendicant knows mind with greed as ‘mind with greed’"

#. </p><p><a class="sc" id="41"></a>
msgctxt "dn22:60.1"
msgid ""
"Vītarāgaṃ vā cittaṃ ‘vītarāgaṃ cittan’ti pajānāti. <span class=\"brnum\""
">(2)</span>"
msgstr "and mind without greed as ‘mind without greed’."

#. </p><p><a class="sc" id="42"></a>
msgctxt "dn22:61.1"
msgid ""
"Sadosaṃ vā cittaṃ ‘sadosaṃ cittan’ti pajānāti. <span class=\"brnum\""
">(3)</span>"
msgstr "They know mind with hate as ‘mind with hate’"

#. </p><p><a class="sc" id="43"></a>
msgctxt "dn22:62.1"
msgid ""
"Vītadosaṃ vā cittaṃ ‘vītadosaṃ cittan’ti pajānāti. <span class=\"brnum\""
">(4)</span>"
msgstr "and mind without hate as ‘mind without hate’."

#. </p><p><a class="sc" id="44"></a>
msgctxt "dn22:63.1"
msgid ""
"Samohaṃ vā cittaṃ ‘samohaṃ cittan’ti pajānāti. <span class=\"brnum\""
">(5)</span>"
msgstr "They know mind with delusion as ‘mind with delusion’"

#. </p><p><a class="sc" id="45"></a>
msgctxt "dn22:64.1"
msgid ""
"Vītamohaṃ vā cittaṃ ‘vītamohaṃ cittan’ti pajānāti. <span class=\"brnum\""
">(6)</span>"
msgstr "and mind without delusion as ‘mind without delusion’."

#. </p><p><a class="sc" id="46"></a>
msgctxt "dn22:65.1"
msgid ""
"Saṅkhittaṃ vā cittaṃ ‘saṅkhittaṃ cittan’ti pajānāti. <span class=\"brnum\""
">(7)</span>"
msgstr "They know contracted mind as ‘contracted mind’"

#. </p><p><a class="sc" id="47"></a>
msgctxt "dn22:66.1"
msgid ""
"Vikkhittaṃ vā cittaṃ ‘vikkhittaṃ cittan’ti pajānāti. <span class=\"brnum\""
">(8)</span>"
msgstr "and scattered mind as ‘scattered mind’."

#. </p><p><a class="sc" id="48"></a>
msgctxt "dn22:67.1"
msgid ""
"Mahaggataṃ vā cittaṃ ‘mahaggataṃ cittan’ti pajānāti. <span class=\"brnum\""
">(9)</span>"
msgstr "They know expansive mind as ‘expansive mind’"

#. </p><p><a class="sc" id="49"></a>
msgctxt "dn22:68.1"
msgid ""
"Amahaggataṃ vā cittaṃ ‘amahaggataṃ cittan’ti pajānāti. <span class=\"brnum\""
">(10)</span>"
msgstr "and unexpansive mind as ‘unexpansive mind’."

#. </p><p><a class="sc" id="50"></a>
msgctxt "dn22:69.1"
msgid ""
"Sauttaraṃ vā cittaṃ ‘sauttaraṃ cittan’ti pajānāti. <span class=\"brnum\""
">(11)</span>"
msgstr "They know mind that is not supreme as ‘mind that is not supreme’"

#. </p><p><a class="sc" id="51"></a>
msgctxt "dn22:70.1"
msgid ""
"Anuttaraṃ vā cittaṃ ‘anuttaraṃ cittan’ti pajānāti. <span class=\"brnum\""
">(12)</span>"
msgstr "and mind that is supreme as ‘mind that is supreme’."

#. </p><p><a class="sc" id="52"></a>
msgctxt "dn22:71.1"
msgid ""
"Samāhitaṃ vā cittaṃ ‘samāhitaṃ cittan’ti pajānāti. <span class=\"brnum\""
">(13)</span>"
msgstr "They know mind immersed in meditation as ‘mind immersed in meditation’,"

#. </p><p><a class="sc" id="53"></a>
msgctxt "dn22:72.1"
msgid ""
"Asamāhitaṃ vā cittaṃ ‘asamāhitaṃ cittan’ti pajānāti. <span class=\"brnum\""
">(14)</span>"
msgstr ""
"and mind not immersed in meditation as ‘mind not immersed in meditation’."

#. </p><p><a class="sc" id="54"></a>
msgctxt "dn22:73.1"
msgid ""
"Vimuttaṃ vā cittaṃ ‘vimuttaṃ cittan’ti pajānāti. <span class=\"brnum\""
">(15)</span>"
msgstr "They know freed mind as ‘freed mind’"

#. </p><p><a class="sc" id="55"></a>
msgctxt "dn22:74.1"
msgid ""
"Avimuttaṃ vā cittaṃ ‘avimuttaṃ cittan’ti pajānāti. <span class=\"brnum\""
">(15)</span>"
msgstr "and unfreed mind as ‘unfreed mind’."

#. </p><p><a class="sc" id="56"></a><a class="pts" id="pts2.300"></a>
msgctxt "dn22:75.1"
msgid ""
"Iti ajjhattaṃ vā citte cittānupassī viharati, bahiddhā vā citte cittānupassī "
"viharati, ajjhattabahiddhā vā citte cittānupassī viharati."
msgstr ""
"And so they meditate observing an aspect of the mind internally, externally, "
"and both internally and externally."

msgctxt "dn22:75.2"
msgid ""
"Samudayadhammānupassī vā cittasmiṃ viharati, vayadhammānupassī vā cittasmiṃ "
"viharati, samudayavayadhammānupassī vā cittasmiṃ viharati, ‘atthi cittan’ti "
"vā panassa sati paccupaṭṭhitā hoti yāvadeva ñāṇamattāya paṭissatimattāya "
"anissito ca viharati, na ca kiñci loke upādiyati."
msgstr ""
"They meditate observing the mind as liable to originate, as liable to "
"vanish, and as liable to both originate and vanish. Or mindfulness is "
"established that the mind exists, to the extent necessary for knowledge and "
"mindfulness. They meditate independent, not grasping at anything in the "
"world."

msgctxt "dn22:75.3"
msgid "Evampi kho, bhikkhave, bhikkhu citte cittānupassī viharati."
msgstr "That’s how a mendicant meditates by observing an aspect of the mind."

#. </p><p class="endsection">
msgctxt "dn22:76.1"
msgid "Cittānupassanā niṭṭhitā."
msgstr ""

#. </p><h2>
msgctxt "dn22:77.1"
msgid "4. Dhammānupassanā"
msgstr "4. Observing Principles"

#. </h2><h3>
msgctxt "dn22:78.1"
msgid "4.1. Dhammānupassanānīvaraṇapabba"
msgstr "4.1. The Hindrances "

#. </h3><p><a class="sc" id="57"></a><a class="wp" id="wp13"></a>
msgctxt "dn22:79.1"
msgid "Kathañca pana, bhikkhave, bhikkhu dhammesu dhammānupassī viharati?"
msgstr ""
"And how does a mendicant meditate by observing an aspect of the principles?"

msgctxt "dn22:79.2"
msgid ""
"Idha, bhikkhave, bhikkhu dhammesu dhammānupassī viharati pañcasu nīvaraṇesu."
msgstr ""
"It’s when a mendicant meditates by observing an aspect of the principles "
"with respect to the five hindrances."

msgctxt "dn22:79.3"
msgid ""
"Kathañca pana, bhikkhave, bhikkhu dhammesu dhammānupassī viharati pañcasu "
"nīvaraṇesu?"
msgstr ""
"And how does a mendicant meditate by observing an aspect of the principles "
"with respect to the five hindrances?"

#. </p><p><a class="sc" id="58"></a>
#, fuzzy
msgctxt "dn22:80.1"
msgid ""
"Idha, bhikkhave, bhikkhu santaṃ vā ajjhattaṃ kāmacchandaṃ ‘atthi me "
"ajjhattaṃ kāmacchando’ti pajānāti, asantaṃ vā ajjhattaṃ kāmacchandaṃ ‘natthi "
"me ajjhattaṃ kāmacchando’ti pajānāti, yathā ca anuppannassa kāmacchandassa "
"uppādo hoti tañca pajānāti, yathā ca uppannassa kāmacchandassa pahānaṃ hoti "
"tañca pajānāti, yathā ca pahīnassa kāmacchandassa āyatiṃ anuppādo hoti tañca "
"pajānāti. <span class=\"brnum\">(1)</span>"
msgstr ""
"It’s when a mendicant who has sensual desire in them understands: ‘I have "
"sensual desire in me.’ When they don’t have sensual desire in them, they "
"understand: ‘I don’t have sensual desire in me.’ They understand how sensual "
"desire arises; how, when it’s already arisen, it’s given up; and how, once "
"it’s given up, it doesn’t arise again in the future."

#. </p><p><a class="sc" id="59"></a>
msgctxt "dn22:81.1"
msgid ""
"Santaṃ vā ajjhattaṃ byāpādaṃ ‘atthi me ajjhattaṃ byāpādo’ti pajānāti, "
"asantaṃ vā ajjhattaṃ byāpādaṃ ‘natthi me ajjhattaṃ byāpādo’ti pajānāti, "
"yathā ca anuppannassa byāpādassa uppādo hoti tañca pajānāti, yathā ca "
"uppannassa byāpādassa pahānaṃ hoti tañca pajānāti, yathā ca pahīnassa "
"byāpādassa āyatiṃ anuppādo hoti tañca pajānāti. <span class=\"brnum\""
">(2)</span>"
msgstr ""
"When they have ill will in them, they understand: ‘I have ill will in me.’ "
"When they don’t have ill will in them, they understand: ‘I don’t have ill "
"will in me.’ They understand how ill will arises; how, when it’s already "
"arisen, it’s given up; and how, once it’s given up, it doesn’t arise again "
"in the future."

#. </p><p><a class="sc" id="60"></a>
msgctxt "dn22:82.1"
msgid ""
"Santaṃ vā ajjhattaṃ thinamiddhaṃ ‘atthi me ajjhattaṃ thinamiddhan’ti "
"pajānāti, asantaṃ vā ajjhattaṃ thinamiddhaṃ ‘natthi me ajjhattaṃ "
"thinamiddhan’ti pajānāti, yathā ca anuppannassa thinamiddhassa uppādo hoti "
"tañca pajānāti, yathā ca uppannassa thinamiddhassa pahānaṃ hoti tañca "
"pajānāti, yathā ca pahīnassa thinamiddhassa āyatiṃ anuppādo hoti tañca "
"pajānāti. <span class=\"brnum\">(3)</span>"
msgstr ""
"When they have dullness and drowsiness in them, they understand: ‘I have "
"dullness and drowsiness in me.’ When they don’t have dullness and drowsiness "
"in them, they understand: ‘I don’t have dullness and drowsiness in me.’ They "
"understand how dullness and drowsiness arise; how, when they’ve already "
"arisen, they’re given up; and how, once they’re given up, they don’t arise "
"again in the future."

#. </p><p><a class="sc" id="61"></a><a class="pts" id="pts2.301"></a>
msgctxt "dn22:83.1"
msgid ""
"Santaṃ vā ajjhattaṃ uddhaccakukkuccaṃ ‘atthi me ajjhattaṃ uddhaccakukkuccan’"
"ti pajānāti, asantaṃ vā ajjhattaṃ uddhaccakukkuccaṃ ‘natthi me ajjhattaṃ "
"uddhaccakukkuccan’ti pajānāti, yathā ca anuppannassa uddhaccakukkuccassa "
"uppādo hoti tañca pajānāti, yathā ca uppannassa uddhaccakukkuccassa pahānaṃ "
"hoti tañca pajānāti, yathā ca pahīnassa uddhaccakukkuccassa āyatiṃ anuppādo "
"hoti tañca pajānāti. <span class=\"brnum\">(4)</span>"
msgstr ""
"When they have restlessness and remorse in them, they understand: ‘I have "
"restlessness and remorse in me.’ When they don’t have restlessness and "
"remorse in them, they understand: ‘I don’t have restlessness and remorse in "
"me.’ They understand how restlessness and remorse arise; how, when they’ve "
"already arisen, they’re given up; and how, once they’re given up, they don’t "
"arise again in the future."

#. </p><p><a class="sc" id="62"></a>
msgctxt "dn22:84.1"
msgid ""
"Santaṃ vā ajjhattaṃ vicikicchaṃ ‘atthi me ajjhattaṃ vicikicchā’ti pajānāti, "
"asantaṃ vā ajjhattaṃ vicikicchaṃ ‘natthi me ajjhattaṃ vicikicchā’ti "
"pajānāti, yathā ca anuppannāya vicikicchāya uppādo hoti tañca pajānāti, "
"yathā ca uppannāya vicikicchāya pahānaṃ hoti tañca pajānāti, yathā ca "
"pahīnāya vicikicchāya āyatiṃ anuppādo hoti tañca pajānāti. <span class=\""
"brnum\">(5)</span>"
msgstr ""
"When they have doubt in them, they understand: ‘I have doubt in me.’ When "
"they don’t have doubt in them, they understand: ‘I don’t have doubt in me.’ "
"They understand how doubt arises; how, when it’s already arisen, it’s given "
"up; and how, once it’s given up, it doesn’t arise again in the future."

#. </p><p><a class="sc" id="63"></a>
msgctxt "dn22:85.1"
msgid ""
"Iti ajjhattaṃ vā dhammesu dhammānupassī viharati, bahiddhā vā dhammesu "
"dhammānupassī viharati, ajjhattabahiddhā vā dhammesu dhammānupassī viharati."
msgstr ""
"And so they meditate observing an aspect of principles internally, "
"externally, and both internally and externally."

msgctxt "dn22:85.2"
msgid ""
"Samudayadhammānupassī vā dhammesu viharati, vayadhammānupassī vā dhammesu "
"viharati, samudayavayadhammānupassī vā dhammesu viharati."
msgstr ""
"They meditate observing the principles as liable to originate, as liable to "
"vanish, and as liable to both originate and vanish."

msgctxt "dn22:85.3"
msgid ""
"‘Atthi dhammā’ti vā panassa sati paccupaṭṭhitā hoti yāvadeva ñāṇamattāya "
"paṭissatimattāya, anissito ca viharati, na ca kiñci loke upādiyati."
msgstr ""
"Or mindfulness is established that principles exist, to the extent necessary "
"for knowledge and mindfulness. They meditate independent, not grasping at "
"anything in the world."

msgctxt "dn22:85.4"
msgid ""
"Evampi kho, bhikkhave, bhikkhu dhammesu dhammānupassī viharati pañcasu "
"nīvaraṇesu."
msgstr ""
"That’s how a mendicant meditates by observing an aspect of the principles "
"with respect to the five hindrances."

#. </p><p class="endsection">
msgctxt "dn22:86.1"
msgid "Nīvaraṇapabbaṃ niṭṭhitaṃ."
msgstr ""

#. </p><h3>
msgctxt "dn22:87.1"
msgid "4.2. Dhammānupassanākhandhapabba"
msgstr "4.2. The Sets of Phenomena"

#. </h3><p><a class="sc" id="64"></a><a class="wp" id="wp14"></a><a class="pts"
#. id="pts2.302"></a>
msgctxt "dn22:88.1"
msgid ""
"Puna caparaṃ, bhikkhave, bhikkhu dhammesu dhammānupassī viharati pañcasu "
"upādānakkhandhesu."
msgstr ""
"Furthermore, a mendicant meditates by observing an aspect of the principles "
"with respect to the five sets of phenomena connected with grasping."

msgctxt "dn22:88.2"
msgid ""
"Kathañca pana, bhikkhave, bhikkhu dhammesu dhammānupassī viharati pañcasu "
"upādānakkhandhesu?"
msgstr ""
"And how does a mendicant meditate by observing an aspect of the principles "
"with respect to the five sets of phenomena connected with grasping?"

msgctxt "dn22:88.3"
msgid "Idha, bhikkhave, bhikkhu:"
msgstr "It’s when a monk contemplates:"

msgctxt "dn22:88.4"
msgid "‘iti rūpaṃ, iti rūpassa samudayo, iti rūpassa atthaṅgamo;"
msgstr ""
"‘Such are physical phenomena, such is the origin of physical phenomena, such "
"is the ending of physical phenomena."

msgctxt "dn22:88.5"
msgid "iti vedanā, iti vedanāya samudayo, iti vedanāya atthaṅgamo;"
msgstr ""
"Such is feeling, such is the origin of feeling, such is the ending of "
"feeling."

msgctxt "dn22:88.6"
msgid "iti saññā, iti saññāya samudayo, iti saññāya atthaṅgamo;"
msgstr ""
"Such is perception, such is the origin of perception, such is the ending of "
"perception."

#, fuzzy
msgctxt "dn22:88.7"
msgid ""
"iti saṅkhārā, iti saṅkhārānaṃ samudayo, iti saṅkhārānaṃ atthaṅgamo, iti "
"viññāṇaṃ, iti viññāṇassa samudayo, iti viññāṇassa atthaṅgamo’ti, iti "
"ajjhattaṃ vā dhammesu dhammānupassī viharati, bahiddhā vā dhammesu "
"dhammānupassī viharati, ajjhattabahiddhā vā dhammesu dhammānupassī viharati."
msgstr ""
"Such are choices, such is the origin of choices, such is the ending of "
"choices. Such is consciousness, such is the origin of consciousness, such is "
"the ending of consciousness.’ And so they meditate observing an aspect of "
"principles internally …"

msgctxt "dn22:88.8"
msgid ""
"Samudayadhammānupassī vā dhammesu viharati, vayadhammānupassī vā dhammesu "
"viharati, samudayavayadhammānupassī vā dhammesu viharati."
msgstr ""

msgctxt "dn22:88.9"
msgid ""
"‘Atthi dhammā’ti vā panassa sati paccupaṭṭhitā hoti yāvadeva ñāṇamattāya "
"paṭissatimattāya, anissito ca viharati, na ca kiñci loke upādiyati."
msgstr ""

msgctxt "dn22:88.10"
msgid ""
"Evampi kho, bhikkhave, bhikkhu dhammesu dhammānupassī viharati pañcasu "
"upādānakkhandhesu."
msgstr ""
"That’s how a mendicant meditates by observing an aspect of the principles "
"with respect to the five sets of phenomena connected with grasping."

#. </p><p class="endsection">
msgctxt "dn22:89.1"
msgid "Khandhapabbaṃ niṭṭhitaṃ."
msgstr ""

#. </p><h3>
msgctxt "dn22:90.1"
msgid "4.3. Dhammānupassanāāyatanapabba"
msgstr "4.3. The Sense Fields"

#. </h3><p><a class="sc" id="65"></a><a class="wp" id="wp15"></a>
msgctxt "dn22:91.1"
msgid ""
"Puna caparaṃ, bhikkhave, bhikkhu dhammesu dhammānupassī viharati chasu "
"ajjhattikabāhiresu āyatanesu."
msgstr ""
"Furthermore, a mendicant meditates by observing an aspect of the principles "
"with respect to the six interior and exterior sense fields."

msgctxt "dn22:91.2"
msgid ""
"Kathañca pana, bhikkhave, bhikkhu dhammesu dhammānupassī viharati chasu "
"ajjhattikabāhiresu āyatanesu?"
msgstr ""
"And how does a mendicant meditate by observing an aspect of the principles "
"with respect to the six interior and exterior sense fields?"

#. </p><p><a class="sc" id="66"></a>
msgctxt "dn22:92.1"
msgid ""
"Idha, bhikkhave, bhikkhu cakkhuñca pajānāti, rūpe ca pajānāti, yañca "
"tadubhayaṃ paṭicca uppajjati saṃyojanaṃ tañca pajānāti, yathā ca "
"anuppannassa saṃyojanassa uppādo hoti tañca pajānāti, yathā ca uppannassa "
"saṃyojanassa pahānaṃ hoti tañca pajānāti, yathā ca pahīnassa saṃyojanassa "
"āyatiṃ anuppādo hoti tañca pajānāti. <span class=\"brnum\">(1)</span>"
msgstr ""
"It’s when a mendicant understands the eye, sights, and the fetter that "
"arises dependent on both of these. They understand how the fetter that has "
"not arisen comes to arise; how the arisen fetter comes to be abandoned; and "
"how the abandoned fetter comes to not rise again in the future."

#. </p><p><a class="sc" id="67"></a>
msgctxt "dn22:93.1"
msgid ""
"Sotañca pajānāti, sadde ca pajānāti, yañca tadubhayaṃ paṭicca uppajjati "
"saṃyojanaṃ tañca pajānāti, yathā ca anuppannassa saṃyojanassa uppādo hoti "
"tañca pajānāti, yathā ca uppannassa saṃyojanassa pahānaṃ hoti tañca "
"pajānāti, yathā ca pahīnassa saṃyojanassa āyatiṃ anuppādo hoti tañca "
"pajānāti. <span class=\"brnum\">(2)</span>"
msgstr "They understand the ear, sounds, and the fetter …"

#. </p><p><a class="sc" id="68"></a>
msgctxt "dn22:94.1"
msgid ""
"Ghānañca pajānāti, gandhe ca pajānāti, yañca tadubhayaṃ paṭicca uppajjati "
"saṃyojanaṃ tañca pajānāti, yathā ca anuppannassa saṃyojanassa uppādo hoti "
"tañca pajānāti, yathā ca uppannassa saṃyojanassa pahānaṃ hoti tañca "
"pajānāti, yathā ca pahīnassa saṃyojanassa āyatiṃ anuppādo hoti tañca "
"pajānāti. <span class=\"brnum\">(3)</span>"
msgstr "They understand the nose, smells, and the fetter …"

#. </p><p><a class="sc" id="69"></a>
msgctxt "dn22:95.1"
msgid ""
"Jivhañca pajānāti, rase ca pajānāti, yañca tadubhayaṃ paṭicca uppajjati "
"saṃyojanaṃ tañca pajānāti, yathā ca anuppannassa saṃyojanassa uppādo hoti "
"tañca pajānāti, yathā ca uppannassa saṃyojanassa pahānaṃ hoti tañca "
"pajānāti, yathā ca pahīnassa saṃyojanassa āyatiṃ anuppādo hoti tañca "
"pajānāti. <span class=\"brnum\">(4)</span>"
msgstr "They understand the tongue, tastes, and the fetter …"

#. </p><p><a class="sc" id="70"></a>
msgctxt "dn22:96.1"
msgid ""
"Kāyañca pajānāti, phoṭṭhabbe ca pajānāti, yañca tadubhayaṃ paṭicca uppajjati "
"saṃyojanaṃ tañca pajānāti, yathā ca anuppannassa saṃyojanassa uppādo hoti "
"tañca pajānāti, yathā ca uppannassa saṃyojanassa pahānaṃ hoti tañca "
"pajānāti, yathā ca pahīnassa saṃyojanassa āyatiṃ anuppādo hoti tañca "
"pajānāti. <span class=\"brnum\">(5)</span>"
msgstr "They understand the body, touches, and the fetter …"

#. </p><p><a class="sc" id="71"></a><a class="pts" id="pts2.303"></a>
msgctxt "dn22:97.1"
msgid ""
"Manañca pajānāti, dhamme ca pajānāti, yañca tadubhayaṃ paṭicca uppajjati "
"saṃyojanaṃ tañca pajānāti, yathā ca anuppannassa saṃyojanassa uppādo hoti "
"tañca pajānāti, yathā ca uppannassa saṃyojanassa pahānaṃ hoti tañca "
"pajānāti, yathā ca pahīnassa saṃyojanassa āyatiṃ anuppādo hoti tañca "
"pajānāti. <span class=\"brnum\">(6)</span>"
msgstr ""
"They understand the mind, thoughts, and the fetter that arises dependent on "
"both of these. They understand how the fetter that has not arisen comes to "
"arise; how the arisen fetter comes to be abandoned; and how the abandoned "
"fetter comes to not rise again in the future."

#. </p><p><a class="sc" id="72"></a>
msgctxt "dn22:98.1"
msgid ""
"Iti ajjhattaṃ vā dhammesu dhammānupassī viharati, bahiddhā vā dhammesu "
"dhammānupassī viharati, ajjhattabahiddhā vā dhammesu dhammānupassī viharati."
msgstr "And so they meditate observing an aspect of principles internally …"

msgctxt "dn22:98.2"
msgid ""
"Samudayadhammānupassī vā dhammesu viharati, vayadhammānupassī vā dhammesu "
"viharati, samudayavayadhammānupassī vā dhammesu viharati."
msgstr ""

msgctxt "dn22:98.3"
msgid ""
"‘Atthi dhammā’ti vā panassa sati paccupaṭṭhitā hoti yāvadeva ñāṇamattāya "
"paṭissatimattāya, anissito ca viharati, na ca kiñci loke upādiyati."
msgstr ""

msgctxt "dn22:98.4"
msgid ""
"Evampi kho, bhikkhave, bhikkhu dhammesu dhammānupassī viharati chasu "
"ajjhattikabāhiresu āyatanesu."
msgstr ""
"That’s how a mendicant meditates by observing an aspect of the principles "
"with respect to the six internal and external sense fields."

#. </p><p class="endsection">
msgctxt "dn22:99.1"
msgid "Āyatanapabbaṃ niṭṭhitaṃ."
msgstr ""

#. </p><h3>
msgctxt "dn22:100.1"
msgid "4.4. Dhammānupassanābojjhaṅgapabba"
msgstr "4.4. The Awakening Factors"

#. </h3><p><a class="sc" id="73"></a><a class="wp" id="wp16"></a>
msgctxt "dn22:101.1"
msgid ""
"Puna caparaṃ, bhikkhave, bhikkhu dhammesu dhammānupassī viharati sattasu "
"bojjhaṅgesu."
msgstr ""
"Furthermore, a mendicant meditates by observing an aspect of the principles "
"with respect to the seven awakening factors."

msgctxt "dn22:101.2"
msgid ""
"Kathañca pana, bhikkhave, bhikkhu dhammesu dhammānupassī viharati sattasu "
"bojjhaṅgesu?"
msgstr ""
"And how does a mendicant meditate by observing an aspect of the principles "
"with respect to the seven awakening factors?"

msgctxt "dn22:101.3"
msgid ""
"Idha, bhikkhave, bhikkhu santaṃ vā ajjhattaṃ satisambojjhaṅgaṃ ‘atthi me "
"ajjhattaṃ satisambojjhaṅgo’ti pajānāti, asantaṃ vā ajjhattaṃ "
"satisambojjhaṅgaṃ ‘natthi me ajjhattaṃ satisambojjhaṅgo’ti pajānāti, yathā "
"ca anuppannassa satisambojjhaṅgassa uppādo hoti tañca pajānāti, yathā ca "
"uppannassa satisambojjhaṅgassa bhāvanāya pāripūrī hoti tañca pajānāti. <span "
"class=\"brnum\">(1)</span>"
msgstr ""
"It’s when a mendicant who has the awakening factor of mindfulness in them "
"understands: ‘I have the awakening factor of mindfulness in me.’ When they "
"don’t have the awakening factor of mindfulness in them, they understand: ‘I "
"don’t have the awakening factor of mindfulness in me.’ They understand how "
"the awakening factor of mindfulness that has not arisen comes to arise; and "
"how the awakening factor of mindfulness that has arisen becomes fulfilled by "
"development."

#. </p><p><a class="sc" id="74"></a>
msgctxt "dn22:102.1"
msgid ""
"Santaṃ vā ajjhattaṃ dhammavicayasambojjhaṅgaṃ ‘atthi me ajjhattaṃ "
"dhammavicayasambojjhaṅgo’ti pajānāti, asantaṃ vā ajjhattaṃ "
"dhammavicayasambojjhaṅgaṃ ‘natthi me ajjhattaṃ dhammavicayasambojjhaṅgo’ti "
"pajānāti, yathā ca anuppannassa dhammavicayasambojjhaṅgassa uppādo hoti "
"tañca pajānāti, yathā ca uppannassa dhammavicayasambojjhaṅgassa bhāvanāya "
"pāripūrī hoti tañca pajānāti. <span class=\"brnum\">(2)</span>"
msgstr "When they have the awakening factor of investigation of principles …"

#. </p><p><a class="sc" id="75"></a>
msgctxt "dn22:103.1"
msgid ""
"Santaṃ vā ajjhattaṃ vīriyasambojjhaṅgaṃ ‘atthi me ajjhattaṃ "
"vīriyasambojjhaṅgo’ti pajānāti, asantaṃ vā ajjhattaṃ vīriyasambojjhaṅgaṃ ‘"
"natthi me ajjhattaṃ vīriyasambojjhaṅgo’ti pajānāti, yathā ca anuppannassa "
"vīriyasambojjhaṅgassa uppādo hoti tañca pajānāti, yathā ca uppannassa "
"vīriyasambojjhaṅgassa bhāvanāya pāripūrī hoti tañca pajānāti. <span class=\""
"brnum\">(3)</span>"
msgstr "energy …"

#. </p><p><a class="sc" id="76"></a>
msgctxt "dn22:104.1"
msgid ""
"Santaṃ vā ajjhattaṃ pītisambojjhaṅgaṃ ‘atthi me ajjhattaṃ pītisambojjhaṅgo’"
"ti pajānāti, asantaṃ vā ajjhattaṃ pītisambojjhaṅgaṃ ‘natthi me ajjhattaṃ "
"pītisambojjhaṅgo’ti pajānāti, yathā ca anuppannassa pītisambojjhaṅgassa "
"uppādo hoti tañca pajānāti, yathā ca uppannassa pītisambojjhaṅgassa "
"bhāvanāya pāripūrī hoti tañca pajānāti. <span class=\"brnum\">(4)</span>"
msgstr "rapture …"

#. </p><p><a class="sc" id="77"></a><a class="pts" id="pts2.304"></a>
msgctxt "dn22:105.1"
msgid ""
"Santaṃ vā ajjhattaṃ passaddhisambojjhaṅgaṃ ‘atthi me ajjhattaṃ "
"passaddhisambojjhaṅgo’ti pajānāti, asantaṃ vā ajjhattaṃ "
"passaddhisambojjhaṅgaṃ ‘natthi me ajjhattaṃ passaddhisambojjhaṅgo’ti "
"pajānāti, yathā ca anuppannassa passaddhisambojjhaṅgassa uppādo hoti tañca "
"pajānāti, yathā ca uppannassa passaddhisambojjhaṅgassa bhāvanāya pāripūrī "
"hoti tañca pajānāti. <span class=\"brnum\">(5)</span>"
msgstr "tranquility …"

#. </p><p><a class="sc" id="78"></a>
msgctxt "dn22:106.1"
msgid ""
"Santaṃ vā ajjhattaṃ samādhisambojjhaṅgaṃ ‘atthi me ajjhattaṃ "
"samādhisambojjhaṅgo’ti pajānāti, asantaṃ vā ajjhattaṃ samādhisambojjhaṅgaṃ ‘"
"natthi me ajjhattaṃ samādhisambojjhaṅgo’ti pajānāti, yathā ca anuppannassa "
"samādhisambojjhaṅgassa uppādo hoti tañca pajānāti, yathā ca uppannassa "
"samādhisambojjhaṅgassa bhāvanāya pāripūrī hoti tañca pajānāti. <span class=\""
"brnum\">(6)</span>"
msgstr "immersion …"

#. </p><p><a class="sc" id="79"></a>
msgctxt "dn22:107.1"
msgid ""
"Santaṃ vā ajjhattaṃ upekkhāsambojjhaṅgaṃ ‘atthi me ajjhattaṃ "
"upekkhāsambojjhaṅgo’ti pajānāti, asantaṃ vā ajjhattaṃ upekkhāsambojjhaṅgaṃ ‘"
"natthi me ajjhattaṃ upekkhāsambojjhaṅgo’ti pajānāti, yathā ca anuppannassa "
"upekkhāsambojjhaṅgassa uppādo hoti tañca pajānāti, yathā ca uppannassa "
"upekkhāsambojjhaṅgassa bhāvanāya pāripūrī hoti tañca pajānāti. <span class=\""
"brnum\">(7)</span>"
msgstr ""
"equanimity in them, they understand: ‘I have the awakening factor of "
"equanimity in me.’ When they don’t have the awakening factor of equanimity "
"in them, they understand: ‘I don’t have the awakening factor of equanimity "
"in me.’ They understand how the awakening factor of equanimity that has not "
"arisen comes to arise; and how the awakening factor of equanimity that has "
"arisen becomes fulfilled by development."

#. </p><p><a class="sc" id="80"></a>
msgctxt "dn22:108.1"
msgid ""
"Iti ajjhattaṃ vā dhammesu dhammānupassī viharati, bahiddhā vā dhammesu "
"dhammānupassī viharati, ajjhattabahiddhā vā dhammesu dhammānupassī viharati."
msgstr ""
"And so they meditate observing an aspect of principles internally, "
"externally, and both internally and externally."

msgctxt "dn22:108.2"
msgid ""
"Samudayadhammānupassī vā dhammesu viharati, vayadhammānupassī vā dhammesu "
"viharati, samudayavayadhammānupassī vā dhammesu viharati."
msgstr ""
"They meditate observing the principles as liable to originate, as liable to "
"vanish, and as liable to both originate and vanish."

msgctxt "dn22:108.3"
msgid ""
"‘Atthi dhammā’ti vā panassa sati paccupaṭṭhitā hoti yāvadeva ñāṇamattāya "
"paṭissatimattāya, anissito ca viharati, na ca kiñci loke upādiyati."
msgstr ""
"Or mindfulness is established that principles exist, to the extent necessary "
"for knowledge and mindfulness. They meditate independent, not grasping at "
"anything in the world."

msgctxt "dn22:108.4"
msgid ""
"Evampi kho, bhikkhave, bhikkhu dhammesu dhammānupassī viharati sattasu "
"bojjhaṅgesu."
msgstr ""
"That’s how a mendicant meditates by observing an aspect of the principles "
"with respect to the seven awakening factors."

#. </p><p class="endsection">
msgctxt "dn22:109.1"
msgid "Bojjhaṅgapabbaṃ niṭṭhitaṃ."
msgstr ""

#. </p><h3>
msgctxt "dn22:110.1"
msgid "4.5. Dhammānupassanāsaccapabba"
msgstr "4.5. The Truths"

#. </h3><p><a class="sc" id="81"></a><a class="wp" id="wp17"></a>
msgctxt "dn22:111.1"
msgid ""
"Puna caparaṃ, bhikkhave, bhikkhu dhammesu dhammānupassī viharati catūsu "
"ariyasaccesu."
msgstr ""
"Furthermore, a mendicant meditates by observing an aspect of the principles "
"with respect to the four noble truths."

msgctxt "dn22:111.2"
msgid ""
"Kathañca pana, bhikkhave, bhikkhu dhammesu dhammānupassī viharati catūsu "
"ariyasaccesu?"
msgstr ""
"And how does a mendicant meditate by observing an aspect of the principles "
"with respect to the four noble truths?"

msgctxt "dn22:111.3"
msgid ""
"Idha, bhikkhave, bhikkhu ‘idaṃ dukkhan’ti yathābhūtaṃ pajānāti, ‘ayaṃ "
"dukkhasamudayo’ti yathābhūtaṃ pajānāti, ‘ayaṃ dukkhanirodho’ti yathābhūtaṃ "
"pajānāti, ‘ayaṃ dukkhanirodhagāminī paṭipadā’ti yathābhūtaṃ pajānāti."
msgstr ""
"It’s when a mendicant truly understands: ‘This is suffering’ … ‘This is the "
"origin of suffering’ … ‘This is the cessation of suffering’ … ‘This is the "
"practice that leads to the cessation of suffering’.  "

#. </p><p class="endsection">
msgctxt "dn22:112.1"
msgid "Paṭhamabhāṇavāro niṭṭhito."
msgstr "The first recitation section is finished."

#. </p><h4>
msgctxt "dn22:113.1"
msgid "4.5.1. Dukkhasaccaniddesa"
msgstr "The Truth of Suffering"

#. </h4><p><a class="sc" id="82"></a><a class="wp" id="wp18"></a><a class="pts"
#. id="pts2.305"></a>
msgctxt "dn22:114.1"
msgid "Katamañca, bhikkhave, dukkhaṃ ariyasaccaṃ?"
msgstr "And what is the noble truth of suffering? "

#. VAR: dukkho → appiyehi ...pe... vippayogo dukkhotipāṭho ceva taṃniddeso ca
#. katthaci na dissati, aṭṭha­ka­thā­yampi taṃsaṃvaṇṇanā
msgctxt "dn22:114.2"
msgid ""
"Jātipi dukkhā, jarāpi dukkhā, maraṇampi dukkhaṃ, "
"sokaparidevadukkhadomanassupāyāsāpi dukkhā, appiyehi sampayogopi dukkho, "
"piyehi vippayogopi dukkho, yampicchaṃ na labhati tampi dukkhaṃ, saṃkhittena "
"pañcupādānakkhandhā dukkhā."
msgstr ""
"Rebirth is suffering; old age is suffering; death is suffering; sorrow, "
"crying, pain, sadness, and distress are suffering; association with the "
"disliked is suffering; separation from the liked is suffering; not getting "
"what you wish for is suffering. In brief, the five sets of phenomena "
"connected with grasping are suffering."

#. </p><p><a class="sc" id="83"></a>
msgctxt "dn22:115.1"
msgid "Katamā ca, bhikkhave, jāti?"
msgstr "And what is rebirth?"

#, fuzzy
msgctxt "dn22:115.2"
msgid ""
"Yā tesaṃ tesaṃ sattānaṃ tamhi tamhi sattanikāye jāti sañjāti okkanti "
"abhinibbatti khandhānaṃ pātubhāvo āyatanānaṃ paṭilābho, ayaṃ vuccati, "
"bhikkhave, jāti. <span class=\"brnum\">(1)</span>"
msgstr ""
"The rebirth, inception, conception, reincarnation, manifestation of the sets "
"of phenomena, and acquisition of the sense fields of the various sentient "
"beings in the various orders of sentient beings. This is called rebirth."

#. </p><p><a class="sc" id="84"></a>
msgctxt "dn22:116.1"
msgid "Katamā ca, bhikkhave, jarā?"
msgstr "And what is old age?"

#, fuzzy
msgctxt "dn22:116.2"
msgid ""
"Yā tesaṃ tesaṃ sattānaṃ tamhi tamhi sattanikāye jarā jīraṇatā khaṇḍiccaṃ "
"pāliccaṃ valittacatā āyuno saṃhāni indriyānaṃ paripāko, ayaṃ vuccati, "
"bhikkhave, jarā. <span class=\"brnum\">(2)</span>"
msgstr ""
"The old age, decrepitude, broken teeth, grey hair, wrinkly skin, diminished "
"vitality, and failing faculties of the various sentient beings in the "
"various orders of sentient beings. This is called old age."

#. </p><p><a class="sc" id="85"></a>
msgctxt "dn22:117.1"
msgid "Katamañca, bhikkhave, maraṇaṃ?"
msgstr "And what is death?"

#. VAR: Yaṃ → yā (s1-3, km)
msgctxt "dn22:117.2"
msgid ""
"Yaṃ tesaṃ tesaṃ sattānaṃ tamhā tamhā sattanikāyā cuti cavanatā bhedo "
"antaradhānaṃ maccu maraṇaṃ kālakiriyā khandhānaṃ bhedo kaḷevarassa nikkhepo "
"jīvitindriyassupacchedo, idaṃ vuccati, bhikkhave, maraṇaṃ. <span class=\""
"brnum\">(3)</span>"
msgstr ""
"The passing away, perishing, disintegration, demise, mortality, death, "
"decease, breaking up of the aggregates, and laying to rest of the corpse of "
"the various sentient beings in the various orders of sentient beings. This "
"is called death."

#. </p><p><a class="sc" id="86"></a><a class="pts" id="pts2.306"></a>
msgctxt "dn22:118.1"
msgid "Katamo ca, bhikkhave, soko?"
msgstr "And what is sorrow?"

msgctxt "dn22:118.2"
msgid ""
"Yo kho, bhikkhave, aññataraññatarena byasanena samannāgatassa "
"aññataraññatarena dukkhadhammena phuṭṭhassa soko socanā socitattaṃ antosoko "
"antoparisoko, ayaṃ vuccati, bhikkhave, soko. <span class=\"brnum\">(4)</span>"
msgstr ""
"The sorrow, sorrowing, state of sorrow, inner sorrow, inner deep sorrow in "
"someone who has undergone misfortune, who has experienced suffering. This is "
"called sorrow."

#. </p><p><a class="sc" id="87"></a>
msgctxt "dn22:119.1"
msgid "Katamo ca, bhikkhave, paridevo?"
msgstr "And what is lamentation."

msgctxt "dn22:119.2"
msgid ""
"Yo kho, bhikkhave, aññataraññatarena byasanena samannāgatassa "
"aññataraññatarena dukkhadhammena phuṭṭhassa ādevo paridevo ādevanā "
"paridevanā ādevitattaṃ paridevitattaṃ, ayaṃ vuccati, bhikkhave, paridevo. <"
"span class=\"brnum\">(5)</span>"
msgstr ""
"The wail, lament, wailing, lamenting, state of wailing and lamentation in "
"someone who has undergone misfortune, who has experienced suffering. This is "
"called lamentation."

#. </p><p><a class="sc" id="88"></a>
msgctxt "dn22:120.1"
msgid "Katamañca, bhikkhave, dukkhaṃ?"
msgstr "And what is pain? "

msgctxt "dn22:120.2"
msgid ""
"Yaṃ kho, bhikkhave, kāyikaṃ dukkhaṃ kāyikaṃ asātaṃ kāyasamphassajaṃ dukkhaṃ "
"asātaṃ vedayitaṃ, idaṃ vuccati, bhikkhave, dukkhaṃ. <span class=\"brnum\""
">(6)</span>"
msgstr ""
"Physical pain, physical displeasure, the painful, unpleasant feeling that’s "
"born from physical contact. This is called suffering."

#. </p><p><a class="sc" id="89"></a>
msgctxt "dn22:121.1"
msgid "Katamañca, bhikkhave, domanassaṃ?"
msgstr "And what is sadness?"

msgctxt "dn22:121.2"
msgid ""
"Yaṃ kho, bhikkhave, cetasikaṃ dukkhaṃ cetasikaṃ asātaṃ manosamphassajaṃ "
"dukkhaṃ asātaṃ vedayitaṃ, idaṃ vuccati, bhikkhave, domanassaṃ. <span class=\""
"brnum\">(7)</span>"
msgstr ""
"Mental pain, mental displeasure, the painful, unpleasant feeling that’s born "
"from mind contact. This is called sadness."

#. </p><p><a class="sc" id="90"></a>
msgctxt "dn22:122.1"
msgid "Katamo ca, bhikkhave, upāyāso?"
msgstr "And what is distress?"

msgctxt "dn22:122.2"
msgid ""
"Yo kho, bhikkhave, aññataraññatarena byasanena samannāgatassa "
"aññataraññatarena dukkhadhammena phuṭṭhassa āyāso upāyāso āyāsitattaṃ "
"upāyāsitattaṃ, ayaṃ vuccati, bhikkhave, upāyāso. <span class=\"brnum\""
">(8)</span>"
msgstr ""
"The stress, distress, state of stress and distress in someone who has "
"undergone misfortune, who has experienced suffering. This is called distress."

#. </p><p><a class="sc" id="91"></a>
msgctxt "dn22:123.1"
msgid "Katamo ca, bhikkhave, appiyehi sampayogo dukkho?"
msgstr "And what is association with the disliked is suffering?"

msgctxt "dn22:123.2"
msgid ""
"Idha yassa te honti aniṭṭhā akantā amanāpā rūpā saddā gandhā rasā phoṭṭhabbā "
"dhammā, ye vā panassa te honti anatthakāmā ahitakāmā aphāsukakāmā "
"ayogakkhemakāmā, yā tehi saddhiṃ saṅgati samāgamo samodhānaṃ missībhāvo, "
"ayaṃ vuccati, bhikkhave, appiyehi sampayogo dukkho. <span class=\"brnum\""
">(9)</span>"
msgstr ""
"There are sights, sounds, smells, tastes, touches, and thoughts that are "
"unlikable, undesirable, and disagreeable. And there are those who want to "
"harm, injure, disturb, and threaten you. The coming together with these, the "
"joining, inclusion, mixing with them: this is called association with the "
"disliked is suffering."

#. </p><p><a class="sc" id="92"></a>
msgctxt "dn22:124.1"
msgid "Katamo ca, bhikkhave, piyehi vippayogo dukkho?"
msgstr "And what is separation from the liked is suffering?"

msgctxt "dn22:124.2"
msgid ""
"Idha yassa te honti iṭṭhā kantā manāpā rūpā saddā gandhā rasā phoṭṭhabbā "
"dhammā, ye vā panassa te honti atthakāmā hitakāmā phāsukakāmā yogakkhemakāmā "
"mātā vā pitā vā bhātā vā bhaginī vā mittā vā amaccā vā ñātisālohitā vā, yā "
"tehi saddhiṃ asaṅgati asamāgamo asamodhānaṃ amissībhāvo, ayaṃ vuccati, "
"bhikkhave, piyehi vippayogo dukkho. <span class=\"brnum\">(10)</span>"
msgstr ""
"There are sights, sounds, smells, tastes, touches, and thoughts that are "
"likable, desirable, and agreeable. And there are those who want to benefit, "
"help, comfort, and protect you. The division from these, the disconnection, "
"segregation, parting from them: this is called separation from the liked is "
"suffering."

#. </p><p><a class="sc" id="93"></a><a class="pts" id="pts2.307"></a>
msgctxt "dn22:125.1"
msgid "Katamañca, bhikkhave, yampicchaṃ na labhati tampi dukkhaṃ?"
msgstr "And what is ‘not getting what you wish for is suffering’?"

msgctxt "dn22:125.2"
msgid "Jātidhammānaṃ, bhikkhave, sattānaṃ evaṃ icchā uppajjati:"
msgstr "In sentient beings who are liable to be reborn, such a wish arises:"

#, fuzzy
msgctxt "dn22:125.3"
msgid "‘aho vata mayaṃ na jātidhammā assāma, na ca vata no jāti āgaccheyyā’ti."
msgstr ""
"‘Oh, if only we were not liable to be reborn! If only rebirth would not come "
"to us!’"

#, fuzzy
msgctxt "dn22:125.4"
msgid ""
"Na kho panetaṃ icchāya pattabbaṃ, idampi yampicchaṃ na labhati tampi dukkhaṃ."
msgstr ""
"But you can’t get that by wishing. This is: ‘not getting what you wish for "
"is suffering.’"

msgctxt "dn22:125.5"
msgid "Jarādhammānaṃ, bhikkhave, sattānaṃ evaṃ icchā uppajjati:"
msgstr "In sentient beings who are liable to grow old …"

msgctxt "dn22:125.6"
msgid "‘aho vata mayaṃ na jarādhammā assāma, na ca vata no jarā āgaccheyyā’ti."
msgstr ""

msgctxt "dn22:125.7"
msgid ""
"Na kho panetaṃ icchāya pattabbaṃ, idampi yampicchaṃ na labhati tampi dukkhaṃ."
msgstr ""

msgctxt "dn22:125.8"
msgid ""
"Byādhidhammānaṃ, bhikkhave, sattānaṃ evaṃ icchā uppajjati ‘aho vata mayaṃ na "
"byādhidhammā assāma, na ca vata no byādhi āgaccheyyā’ti."
msgstr "fall ill …"

msgctxt "dn22:125.9"
msgid ""
"Na kho panetaṃ icchāya pattabbaṃ, idampi yampicchaṃ na labhati tampi dukkhaṃ."
msgstr ""

msgctxt "dn22:125.10"
msgid ""
"Maraṇadhammānaṃ, bhikkhave, sattānaṃ evaṃ icchā uppajjati ‘aho vata mayaṃ na "
"maraṇadhammā assāma, na ca vata no maraṇaṃ āgaccheyyā’ti."
msgstr "die …"

msgctxt "dn22:125.11"
msgid ""
"Na kho panetaṃ icchāya pattabbaṃ, idampi yampicchaṃ na labhati tampi dukkhaṃ."
msgstr ""

#, fuzzy
msgctxt "dn22:125.12"
msgid ""
"Sokaparidevadukkhadomanassupāyāsadhammānaṃ, bhikkhave, sattānaṃ evaṃ icchā "
"uppajjati ‘aho vata mayaṃ na sokaparidevadukkhadomanassupāyāsadhammā assāma, "
"na ca vata no sokaparidevadukkhadomanassupāyāsaā āgaccheyyun’ti."
msgstr ""
"experience sorrow, lamentation, pain, sadness, and distress, such a wish "
"arises: ‘Oh, if only we were not liable to experience sorrow, lamentation, "
"pain, sadness, and distress! If only sorrow, lamentation, pain, sadness, and "
"distress would not come to us!’"

msgctxt "dn22:125.13"
msgid ""
"Na kho panetaṃ icchāya pattabbaṃ, idampi yampicchaṃ na labhati tampi "
"dukkhaṃ. <span class=\"brnum\">(11)</span>"
msgstr ""
"But you can’t get that by wishing. This is: ‘not getting what you wish for "
"is suffering.’"

#. </p><p><a class="sc" id="94"></a>
msgctxt "dn22:126.1"
msgid "Katame ca, bhikkhave, saṅkhittena pañcupādānakkhandhā dukkhā?"
msgstr ""
"And what is ‘in brief, the five sets of phenomena connected with grasping "
"are suffering’?"

msgctxt "dn22:126.2"
msgid "Seyyathidaṃ—"
msgstr "They are"

msgctxt "dn22:126.3"
msgid ""
"rūpupādānakkhandho, vedanupādānakkhandho, saññupādānakkhandho, "
"saṅkhārupādānakkhandho, viññāṇupādānakkhandho."
msgstr ""
"the sets of phenomena connected with grasping that consist of physical "
"phenomena, feeling, perception, choices, and consciousness."

msgctxt "dn22:126.4"
msgid "Ime vuccanti, bhikkhave, saṅkhittena pañcupādānakkhandhā dukkhā."
msgstr ""
"This is called ‘in brief, the five sets of phenomena connected with grasping "
"are suffering.’"

msgctxt "dn22:126.5"
msgid "Idaṃ vuccati, bhikkhave, dukkhaṃ ariyasaccaṃ."
msgstr "This is called the noble truth of suffering."

#. </p><h4>
msgctxt "dn22:127.1"
msgid "4.5.2. Samudayasaccaniddesa"
msgstr "The Origin of Suffering"

#. </h4><p><a class="sc" id="95"></a><a class="wp" id="wp19"></a><a class="pts"
#. id="pts2.308"></a>
msgctxt "dn22:128.1"
msgid "Katamañca, bhikkhave, dukkhasamudayaṃ ariyasaccaṃ?"
msgstr "And what is the noble truth of the origin of suffering?"

#. VAR: ponobbhavikā → ponobhavikā (bj, pts1)
msgctxt "dn22:128.2"
msgid ""
"Yāyaṃ taṇhā ponobbhavikā nandīrāgasahagatā tatratatrābhinandinī, seyyathidaṃ—"
msgstr ""
"It’s the craving that leads to future rebirth, mixed up with relishing and "
"greed, looking for enjoyment in various different realms. That is,"

msgctxt "dn22:128.3"
msgid "kāmataṇhā bhavataṇhā vibhavataṇhā."
msgstr ""
"craving for sensual pleasures, craving for continued existence, and craving "
"to terminate existence."

#. </p><p><a class="sc" id="96"></a>
msgctxt "dn22:129.1"
msgid ""
"Sā kho panesā, bhikkhave, taṇhā kattha uppajjamānā uppajjati, kattha "
"nivisamānā nivisati?"
msgstr "But where does that craving arise and where does it settle?"

msgctxt "dn22:129.2"
msgid ""
"Yaṃ loke piyarūpaṃ sātarūpaṃ, etthesā taṇhā uppajjamānā uppajjati, ettha "
"nivisamānā nivisati."
msgstr ""
"Whatever in the world seems nice and pleasant, it is there that craving "
"arises and settles."

#. </p><p><a class="sc" id="97"></a>
